e unit). A barangay consists of less than 1,000 inhabitants residing within a city or municipality. A barangay is administered by a set of elected officials who are led by a chairperson. The Human Development Report (UNDP 2003) classifies the Philippines as a middle-level country on the human development index, positioning it in the range of 70th to 110th.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "d0bd5d7b-a8f6-4b1b-b870-d871c77d7ba2": {"__data__": {"id_": "d0bd5d7b-a8f6-4b1b-b870-d871c77d7ba2", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/energy-and-poverty-philippines", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Energy and Poverty in the Philippines", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/energy-and-poverty-philippines", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "71591e7278582e8c883dad07b9b84fba96ff8fc49b73e45237c95994dc95b4bb"}, "2": {"node_id": "d991da64-196c-44dd-9054-119071f299f7", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/energy-and-poverty-philippines", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "4ef228ff4f0cdf96638df38978b35f818b27d27115c06ebb8a02e2909cd7760f"}}, "hash": "d74f6bf46deae1e9036f749ae6bea596d4e9b234407a7bf2be55dd7412abf071", "text": "In terms of the human poverty index, the ENERGY AND POVERTY IN THE PHILIPPINES Challenges and the Way Forward BACKGROUND 1 Energy and Poverty in the Philippines Sources IE