e discount rate or the interest rate is the rate (as a percentage) to be used for valuing the invest- ments made or cost incurred in creating physical assets. This depicts the time value of money. For example, if a certain amount is invested in a bank, the return one would expect at the end of the term is determined by this rate. This varies according to individuals, countries and investment alternatives. The discount rate to be used here is the average for the country. This is estimated based on prevailing inflation rates, bank interest rates, etc.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "eac3b813-db54-4a5c-8904-a49de743f51c": {"__data__": {"id_": "eac3b813-db54-4a5c-8904-a49de743f51c", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/energy-costing-tool-user-guide", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Energy Costing Tool: User Guide", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/energy-costing-tool-user-guide", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "f83db9cda933cb5e3861996bb317a43c28404a1747c71bb5ec7d9c8eaad1d785"}, "2": {"node_id": "be315ae2-820d-4e77-bcca-66bc4571011c", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/energy-costing-tool-user-guide", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "a26868c69b9b51e1503b50cb44e7efa0bb6e0bdf351053e335fa9547f974df3f"}}, "hash": "39fd04dd369687540cc6d77df1ce28d87d4286b44858c070a0e204d2