programmes. The number of such one-day programmes should be decided based on country-specific requirements. 2. Senior-level empowerment programmes: The target audience would be senior bureaucrats, lead- ers of industry/civil society organizations, senior officials and managers. This could be a two-day programme with expert talks, panel discussions, experience sharing and group discussion sessions. The purpose would be to build capacity to successfully implement programmes. Again the number of such programmes would depend on the individual needs of a country. 3. Advanced middle-level empowerment programmes: The programme would target middle-level managers and officials. This could be a two-week programme (including days off) with techni- cal sessions, panel discussions, group discussions, group/individual exercises, field visits, etc. The purpose of the programme would be to build capacity to effectively implement and manage pro- grammes. The number of such programmes would depend on the individual needs of a country. 4. Basic operational-level skills building programmes: The target audience would be junior operational officers, technicians, and user groups. This could be a longer duration three-week pro- gramme with both classroom and field training. The focus should be on skills-building to operate and maintain the necessary equipment. The number of such programmes would depend on the requirements of a country. 5. Course programmes for new talent creation: The course programme would target pro- spective students who could become future managers, leaders, etc. This should be planned as a one-year diploma programme (both a diploma and a post-graduate diploma). The purpose of this programme would be to create a pool of talent to serve the energy sector keeping the emphasis on MDGs, sustainable development and energy access. This would have to be a course programme with a well-structured syllabus and evaluation system, offered by a university. 6. Enabling documents: All stakeholders would be the target audience. The documents would focus on issues related to regulatory, policy and institutional mechanisms. In addition, training man- uals would need to be prepared covering all the required topics. These training manuals should cater to the needs of all training programmes. 7. Information dissemination: Information packages consisting of brochures, newsletters, audio and video material, papers and reports need to be developed. These packages may be an effective way of building large-scale capacity to make optimal choices with respect to accessing modern energy services.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "f0474bc3-4bb0-453e-ab0e-abdf83a8e14f": {"__data__": {"id_": "f0474bc3-4bb0-453e-ab0e-abdf83a8e14f", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/energy-costing-tool-user-guide", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Energy Costing Tool: User Guide", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/energy-costing-tool-user-guide", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "697f223d25a06e8ff81f1d2b8c59906597fce29862fd9f4264309a03bdd7b4c7"}, "2": {"node_id": "ae1bd76e-1904-40e1-a2ab-00fe74040371", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/energy-costing-tool-user-guide", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "a51083645f34fd32886e3be57937dea2b24165b98e5938eaf15c63c6af378ed7"}}, "hash": "f347efe2170fdcdb12a090e5abf86389c0b3c32076d308dec684892d54a8bdc9", "text": "The target audience would be the general public and stakeholders. 8. E-information base: A website fully dedicated to disseminating knowledge on issues related to energy access should be developed, providing all the documentation developed for the above programmes. The costing of", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "05511c96-90fc-4267-bfb8-46186e92f1b3": {"__data__": {"id_": "05511c96-90fc-4267-bfb8-46186e92f1b3", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/energy-costing-tool-user-guide", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Energy Costing Tool: User Guide", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/energy-costing-tool-user-guide", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "288c8c5d34188049201735887ceb9f9416350c94e8a7d3d5e092c5934464e0a6"}, "3": {"node_id": "cb61c04b-c618-4709-9530-e92fecab0810", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/energy-costing-tool-user-guide", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "b1121752c120d0301f39ac33fcb2f7f23ea776f777db30b21f6916b5e6f98a3d"}}, "hash": "077924818344751dc219c8668a892405d7bcbc8011c6df13c2d3894d99dcdf6e", "text": "capacity development programmes (Table 19) needs to be carried out including all the possible costs related to logistics, experts\u2019 time, document preparation, etc. The descri